41
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:57,200
- You saw that? - No, but I saw the previews.
-你有看吗？ -没有，但是我看了预告

42
00:02:57,370 --> 00:03:00,570
They played it right before Jackass.
他们在《蠢蛋搞怪秀》播出之前有预告

43
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:03,140
- He's done some amazing work. - Oh, yeah.
-他做了些挺好的东西 -喔，是啊

44
00:03:03,310 --> 00:03:05,510
I loved him in those phone commercials.
我喜欢他的电话广告演出

45
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:09,580
When the monkey hits him in the face with the giant rubber phone..
猴子用巨形塑胶电话打他的脸

46
00:03:09,820 --> 00:03:11,680
Maybe the monkey will be at the audition.
或许猴子也会在试演会上

47
00:03:11,890 --> 00:03:15,650
Don't make me more nervous than I already am!
别让我再更紧张了！

48
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:27,360
- Good morning. - Can I get you a cup of coffee, sir?
-早安 -我可以帮您倒咖啡吗？先生

49
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:30,500
Oh, no, no. I'm an intern, just like you guys.
喔，不，我是实习生 就跟你们一样

50
00:03:30,670 --> 00:03:35,230
Except for the tie, the briefcase and the fact that I can rent a car.
除了这领带，公事包，还有我已到达 合法年龄可以租车以外

51
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:37,240
Seriously, you're an intern?
真的？你是实习生？

52
00:03:37,450 --> 00:03:41,540
I'm heading in a new career direction and you gotta start at the bottom.
我正在转换职业跑道中 得要从基层做起

53
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:44,210
Dude.
老兄

54
00:03:44,620 --> 00:03:49,850
I know I'm a little older than you guys, but it's not like I'm Bob Hope.
我知道我比你们大一些 但不至于像许不了一样

55
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:54,890
The comedian. USO.
从前的一位喜剧演员，“小伯乐”

56
00:03:56,530 --> 00:04:00,020
It's U.S.A., sir.
先生，是“老伯”了

57
00:04:05,910 --> 00:04:08,930
This is Joey Tribbiani. Joey, these are the producers.
这位是乔伊崔比亚尼 乔伊，这几位都是制作人

58
00:04:09,110 --> 00:04:12,080
And as you probably already know, this is Leonard Hayes.
而你或许早就知道了 这位是李奥海斯

59
00:04:16,220 --> 00:04:21,250
It is so amazing to meet you. I am such a big fan of your work.
能够见到你真是太惊喜了 我是你的超级影迷

60
00:04:21,460 --> 00:04:24,290
I've been blessed with a lot of great roles.
我很幸运能够演出许多很棒的角色

61
00:04:24,730 --> 00:04:29,630
Tell me about it, huh? "Unlimited nights and weekends!"
那倒是没错，“不限分钟 不限时数！”

62
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:34,100
Are you making fun of me? Because I am not a sellout.
你是在取笑我吗？ 我可是真的在为他们背书

63
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:36,960
I didn't do it for money. I believe in those phones!
我不是为钱而做的 我相信他们的电话好用！

64
00:04:37,140 --> 00:04:41,510
I almost lost a cousin because of bad wireless service.
一家很烂的大哥大电话公司 害我差点失去一个表哥

65
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:45,840
No, I wasn't making fun of you. I think you were great in those commercials.
不，我不是在取笑你 我认为你在广告里的演出很棒

66
00:04:46,010 --> 00:04:47,350
- Really? - Yeah.
-真的？ -是的

67
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:50,610
Well, I do bring a certain credibility to the role.
嗯，我倒是真的有说服力扮演那角色

68
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:54,980
Are you kidding? When they shoot you out of that cannon..
何止如此 当他们拍摄你从火箭筒冲出来时…

69
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:58,490
"Hang up that phone!"
“挂掉那个电话！”

70
00:04:58,660 --> 00:05:01,820
- One take. - Wow.
-一次就拍成 -哇

71
00:05:02,030 --> 00:05:05,020
- So shall we read? - Oh, yeah, sure.
-那我们要开始了吗？ -喔，是的，当然

72
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:09,260
Top of Act 2. This is my entrance. You got it?
第二幕开始，我会出场，知道吗？

73
00:05:12,810 --> 00:05:15,440
What the hell are you still doing here?
你为什么还愣在这里？

74
00:05:18,010 --> 00:05:20,410
- I think you know. - Bastard!
-我想你知道 -浑蛋！

75
00:05:20,620 --> 00:05:24,110
I am what you made me. You know what? I could go right now.
这都是你造成的 你知道吗？我现在就可以走

76
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:26,980
- Go! Go! - I can't.
-走！走！ -我不行

77
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:30,850
Oh, I want to, Long Pause..
喔，我想要，长暂停…

78
00:05:33,030 --> 00:05:35,150
but I can't.
但是我不行

79
00:05:36,030 --> 00:05:42,060
So sorry. You're not supposed to say "long pause."
很抱歉，但是你不应该说出“长暂停”

80
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:48,140
Oh! Oh, I thought that was your character's name. You know?
喔！喔，我以为那是你角色的名字

81
00:05:48,310 --> 00:05:51,800
I thought you were, like, an Indian or something, you know, with the..
我以为你可能是印地安人 你知道的，名字都是…

82
00:05:53,550 --> 00:05:57,680
No. Thank you so much for coming in. We appreciate it. Thank you.
不，谢谢你过来，我们很感激，谢谢

83
00:05:57,850 --> 00:05:59,680
You don't want me to do it again?
你不要我再演一次吗？

84
00:05:59,850 --> 00:06:01,480
- I could do an accent. - No.
-我可以加上口音喔 -不用了

85
00:06:01,660 --> 00:06:06,720
You know, Southern. "l could go right now, mon!" Huh?
你知道的，南方的口音 “我可以现在就走，老兄！”怎样？

86
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:11,660
My God in heaven.
我的老天爷啊

87
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:17,100
Joey, hang on. Leonard, can we talk to you for a moment?
乔伊，等一下 李奥，我们可以跟你谈一下吗？

88
00:06:17,270 --> 00:06:23,470
Yes? You've got to be kidding. He can't act.
怎样？你是在开玩笑吧 他根本不会演戏

89
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:25,370
I don't care if you think he's hot.
我不在乎你是不是觉得他很帅

90
00:06:25,550 --> 00:06:30,210
If you want to sleep with him, do it on your own time. This is a play.
如果你想要跟他上床，随你便 但是这是一场戏剧表演

91
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:32,680
If you insist on this..
如果你坚持这样…

92
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:34,880
I will call my agent so fast..
我会马上打电话给我的经纪人

93
00:06:35,060 --> 00:06:38,890
on a cell phone connection so clear, he's gonna think I'm next door!
用话质清晰的大哥大打 让他以为我人就在隔壁！

94
00:06:40,730 --> 00:06:45,290
Hi, thank you so much for whispering for my benefit.
嗨，谢谢你这么小声帮我说话

95
00:06:45,530 --> 00:06:49,940
Tell me what I did wrong. I'd love to work on it and try it again for you.
跟我说我是哪里不好 我会改进，然后再表演一次给你看

96
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:52,300
And also, how you doing?
还有，你好吗？

97
00:06:55,780 --> 00:07:00,270
Give me another chance. I really want to get better. Please?
再给我一次机会 我真的想要改进，拜托

98
00:07:01,820 --> 00:07:04,050
If you want to come back today..
如果你想要明天再回来

99
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:05,950
- here are my notes. Ready? - Yeah.
-这是我的建议，准备好了吗？ -好了

100
00:07:06,150 --> 00:07:11,890
- You're in your head. Thinking too much. - I really doubt that.
-你在你的脑子里，想太多了 -我真的很怀疑

101
00:07:12,090 --> 00:07:15,790
No, no. It's that you're not connected with anything in your body.
不是，你并没有跟你的身体做连结

102
00:07:16,030 --> 00:07:18,230
There's no urgency. The scene is a struggle.
没表达出迫切感，这一幕是很挣扎的

103
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:21,930
It's a race. Also, what you did was horizontal.
是一种竞赛，还有 你的表演是水平的

104
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:25,040
Don't be afraid to explore the vertical.
别害怕发掘垂直的情感

105
00:07:25,470 --> 00:07:30,470
And don't learn the words. Let the words learn you.
而且不要体会那些文字 让文字体会你

106
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:37,340
Couldn't I just sleep with the producer?
我不能跟制作人睡一睡就好了吗？

107
00:07:41,394 --> 00:07:45,558
我快不行了，快爆炸了

108
00:07:49,030 --> 00:07:51,120
Hey, do you want to go to dinner tonight?
嘿，要不要一起去吃晚餐？

109
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:55,130
I can't. I've got a date with that waitress, Katie.
不行，我要跟那个女服务生凯蒂约会

110
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:58,470
I know we've only gone out, like, twice, but I don't know..
我们只有出去过好像两次 但是我不知道…

111
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:03,580
- I have a good feeling about her. - Oh, I hear divorce bells.
-我对她的印象很不错 -喔，我听到离婚的声音了

112
00:08:03,810 --> 00:08:06,470
Give me your wallets, and there won't be a problem.
钱包给我，不然你们就惨了

113
00:08:06,650 --> 00:08:08,410
- What? - I have a gun.
-什么？ -我有枪

114
00:08:08,650 --> 00:08:11,810
Okay, relax, Phoebe. Just stay calm.
好的，不要怕，菲比 冷静一点

115
00:08:13,790 --> 00:08:16,220
Oh, my God, I can't find my wallet!
我的天，我找不到皮夹子！

116
00:08:18,190 --> 00:08:21,890
- All right, lady, now give me your purse. - No.
-好了，女士，该你把皮包给我了 -不要

117
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:26,190
What do you mean "no"? I knew you'd be my death, Phoebe Buffay!
“不要”？你是什么意思？我就知道 我会死在你手上，菲比布菲！

118
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:29,900
- Lowell, is that you? - Phoebe?
-罗威，是你吗？ -菲比？

119
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:34,770
- Oh, my God! - Unbelievable! Oh, my God!
-喔，我的天啊！ -真不敢相信，我的天啊！

120
00:08:34,940 --> 00:08:39,400
I'm sorry. Ross, this is my old friend, Lowell, from the streets!
我很抱歉，罗斯， 这是我街头的老朋友，罗威

121
00:08:39,580 --> 00:08:42,010
- Lowell, Ross. - Ross, nice to meet you.
-罗威，这位是罗斯 -罗斯，很高兴认识你

122
00:08:42,220 --> 00:08:44,340
Yeah, a real pleasure.
是啊，真是高兴

123
00:08:45,090 --> 00:08:48,750
It's been so long! Oh, so long.
真是好久了，哇，真久

124
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:52,410
- I can't believe you're still doing this. - I know. But I quit smoking.
-不敢相信你还在干这行 -我知道，但是我戒烟了

125
00:08:52,630 --> 00:08:54,390
Good for you.
好极了

126
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:56,260
You look like you're doing well.
你看起来好像过得不错

127
00:08:56,460 --> 00:08:59,060
I guess your mugging days are behind you.
我猜抢劫的日子对你而言 已经是过去式了

128
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:02,600
Oh, my God. Phoebe, you used to mug people?
我的天，菲比 你以前会抢劫人？

129
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:07,040
Excuse me, Ross, old friends catching up.
对不起，罗斯 我们老朋友正在叙旧耶

130
00:09:12,450 --> 00:09:15,900
- How'd the audition go? - They want to see me again, but..
-试演进行得如何呢？ -他们要我再去，但是…

131
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:18,810
Leonard Hayes did not like me.
李奥海斯并不喜欢我

132
00:09:18,990 --> 00:09:22,650
- What happened? - He said I wasn't urgent enough.
-怎么了？ -他说我迫切感不够

133
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:28,660
Everything I did was horizontal, and I should be more vertical.
我演的是水平的 应该要垂直一点

134
00:09:28,930 --> 00:09:34,460
- He said that I should think less. - Well, so far so good.
-他说我应该不要想太多 -喔，目前为止还不错啊

135
00:09:34,670 --> 00:09:36,800
Honey, I'm old!
亲爱的，我老了！

136
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:40,030
I didn't know you were coming home for lunch.
我不知道你要回家吃中饭 

137
00:09:40,210 --> 00:09:43,270
- Can I get you anything? - Sure, a tube of Polident?
-想要来点什么吗？ -当然，假牙清洁剂…

138
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:46,240
Some Depends?
包大人纸尿布

139
00:09:46,410 --> 00:09:48,810
Birthday wishes from Willard Scott.
白光唱的生日快乐歌

140
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:50,540
What's wrong?
怎么了？

141
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:54,350
I am so much older than these other interns. I can't compete with them.
我比其他的实习生老太多了 我无法跟他们竞争

142
00:09:55,020 --> 00:09:56,390
So you're a little older.
你是年纪比较大一点没错

143
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:59,420
Look at the positive. You have all this life experience.
往好处想，你有更多的生活经历

144
00:09:59,630 --> 00:10:05,190
Yes, but I don't think life experience is gonna help me with these.
是的，但是我不认为生活经历 可以帮助我这个

145
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:11,300
Wow! It's like they're on fire!
哇！它们就像着火了！

146
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:18,230
- What are they? - Prototype sneakers.
-这些是什么？ -样品鞋

147
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:20,900
I need ideas on how to sell them. Which I can't do..
我需要想出该怎么卖 而我办不到

148
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:23,710
because no self-respecting adult would ever wear these.
因为有自尊的成人不会穿这种东西的

149
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:25,510
I'll give you $500 for them.
我给你五百块买下这双

150
00:10:29,590 --> 00:10:32,620
- What am I supposed to do? - Come on, sneakers are easy.
-我应该怎么办呢？ -别这样，步鞋很容易啦！

151
00:10:32,790 --> 00:10:36,490
- You wear them all the time. - They're not called sneakers anymore.
-你也常常在穿啊 -它们现在不叫做步鞋了

152
00:10:36,660 --> 00:10:42,600
They're called "kicks" or "skids." I think I heard somebody say "slorps."
改叫“溜鞋”或是“滑轮鞋” 我还听到有人说“轮鞋”

153
00:10:44,140 --> 00:10:47,900
They've got wheels that pop out from the bottom so you can roll around..
它们底部有轮子突出来 让你可以滑来滑去

154
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:51,480
because apparently walking is too much exercise.
因为很显然，走路太耗费体力了

155
00:10:51,650 --> 00:10:56,050
"Kids! Kids! Roll your way to childhood obesity!"
“孩子们！孩子们！ 向前滑到儿童肥胖区吧！”

156
00:10:57,920 --> 00:11:01,150
Kids today have such an easier time getting fat.
这年头小孩子要变胖可真快啊！

157
00:11:03,660 --> 00:11:05,850
Would you help me try to sell these?
你可以帮我卖这些东西吗？

158
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:11,090
Okay. Have you considered using a girl with huge knockers?
好的，有没有想过用大波霸呢？

159
00:11:11,900 --> 00:11:13,760
That's not what they're looking for.
那不会是他们想要的

160
00:11:13,970 --> 00:11:16,490
Hey, that would work on me.
嘿，那对我很有用喔

161
00:11:16,670 --> 00:11:18,730
Why do you think I buy Mrs. Butterworth's?
你想我为什么要买津津芦笋汁呢？

162
00:11:25,985 --> 00:11:27,475
（中央咖啡厅）

163
00:11:29,450 --> 00:11:31,750
You'll never guess what just happened.
你不会相信刚刚发生什么事

164
00:11:31,920 --> 00:11:34,580
- Phoebe and I got mugged! - Are you okay?
-菲比跟我被抢了 -你们没事吧

165
00:11:34,790 --> 00:11:37,380
Yeah. Phoebe knew the mugger.
没事，因为菲比认识那个抢匪

166
00:11:38,260 --> 00:11:39,620
How do you know a mugger?
你怎么会认识抢匪呢？

167
00:11:39,830 --> 00:11:44,090
I'm sorry, I have friends outside the six of us.
不好意思，除了我们六个人之外 我还是有其他朋友的

168
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:47,390
Know how she knew him? Because Phoebe used to mug people.
你知道他们是怎么认识的吗？ 因为菲比以前也是在抢劫别人

169
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:49,300
Seriously?
真的吗？

170
00:11:49,470 --> 00:11:53,000
Well, I'm not proud of it, but, you know..
我不觉得很光荣，但是你们知道的

171
00:11:53,170 --> 00:11:58,410
when I was living on the street and I needed money for food and stuff..
当我流落街头的时候 我也需要钱买食物之类的东西

172
00:11:58,610 --> 00:12:02,480
- That is awful. - I wasn't rich like you guys, okay?
-真是太糟糕了 -我不像你们那么有钱，好吗？

173
00:12:02,650 --> 00:12:06,710
I didn't eat gold and have a flying pony.
我没有金汤匙也没有飞天马

174
00:12:06,950 --> 00:12:11,050
I had a hard life. My mother was killed by a drug dealer.
我的生活很苦 我妈被毒贩给杀了

175
00:12:11,290 --> 00:12:16,030
- Your mother killed herself. - She was a drug dealer.
-你妈是自杀的 -她自己就是毒贩

176
00:12:16,860 --> 00:12:21,820
It was a good thing she knew him. I was about to do some serious damage.
幸好菲比认识他 否则我会让他死得很难看

177
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:23,440
Okay.
好吧

178
00:12:25,070 --> 00:12:28,060
This must have brought back some bad memories for you, Ross.
这一定让你想起不好的回忆，罗斯

179
00:12:28,310 --> 00:12:31,070
- Why? - Ross was mugged as a kid.
-为什么？ -罗斯小时候被抢过

180
00:12:31,310 --> 00:12:34,540
- You were? - Yeah. And it was pretty traumatic.
-是吗？ -是的，受到非常严重的创伤

181
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:36,880
It was outside St. Mark's Comics.
就在漫画王外面

182
00:12:37,050 --> 00:12:42,050
I was minding my business, seeing what kind of trouble Spider-Man was into.
我正在做我自己的事 看蜘蛛人又惹上什么麻烦了

183
00:12:42,260 --> 00:12:44,320
Wonder Woman.
是神力女超人

184
00:12:45,490 --> 00:12:47,590
Anyway, I was heading towards this bakery..
反正，我正在要去面包店的路上

185
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:52,460
to pick up a couple of dozen linzer tortes for someone..
帮某人买几个蛋糕

186
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:57,690
when out of nowhere, this thug with a pipe jumps out and says:
然后不知道从哪里冒出来的恶棍 拿着一条管子跳出来说…

187
00:12:57,870 --> 00:13:00,170
- "Give me your money, punk!" - Oh, my God.
-“小子！钱交出来” -喔，我的天啊

188
00:13:00,340 --> 00:13:03,210
I know. And the worst part was, they took my backpack..
我知道，最糟糕的是 他们抢走了我的背包

189
00:13:03,380 --> 00:13:09,210
which had all the original artwork I did for my own comic book, Science Boy.
里面有我自己画的漫画，《科学小子》

190
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:12,580
Oh, yeah! What was his super power again?
对啊，他的超能力是什么？

191
00:13:12,790 --> 00:13:15,690
A super-human thirst for knowledge.
一个渴望知识的超人

192
00:13:17,890 --> 00:13:19,420
I better get to class.
我要赶去上课了

193
00:13:19,590 --> 00:13:22,790
Are there any more of your friends I should look out for?
你还有其他朋友我需要小心的吗，菲比？

194
00:13:23,030 --> 00:13:26,090
No. Actually, you might want to stay away from Jane Street.
没有，事实上 你或许得离詹恩街远点

195
00:13:26,270 --> 00:13:30,000
That's where Stabby Joe works.
那是刺客乔的地盘

196
00:13:32,940 --> 00:13:35,770
- I think we have a problem here. - What?
-我想我们有麻烦了 -怎么了？

197
00:13:36,010 --> 00:13:41,110
Back in my mugging days, I worked St. Mark's Comics.
在我当抢匪的时候 漫画王是我的地盘

198
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:45,810
- Yeah? - A pipe was my weapon of choice..
-是吗？ -我用的武器是管子

199
00:13:46,020 --> 00:13:49,150
and preteen, comic-book nerds were my meat.
而且小孩子、漫画书虫 都是我的目标

200
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:52,020
So?
所以呢？

201
00:13:52,230 --> 00:13:55,660
There was one kid who had a sticker on his backpack that said:
有一个小孩子 在背包上有张贴纸写着…

202
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:58,090
- "Geology rocks!" - "Geology rocks!"
-“地质学酷毙了！” -“地质学酷毙了！”

203
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:05,140
- Oh, my God! - I know! I mugged Ross!
-喔，我的天啊！ -我知道！我抢了罗斯！

204
00:14:10,210 --> 00:14:12,150
- You're late. - I know. I'm sorry.
-你迟到了 -我知道，我很抱歉

205
00:14:12,310 --> 00:14:14,040
But can I just run to the bathroom?
但是我可以先去上厕所吗？

206
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:18,270
- No. Leonard doesn't wait. - But I am bursting with Yoo-hoo!
-不行，李奥是不等人的 -但是我快尿出来了！

207
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:22,150
Joey, here we go! Let's go. Very quickly.
乔伊，来吧！ 我们开始，快一点

208
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:24,720
- I really need.. - We must go now, quickly.
-我真的想要… -我们现在就得开始，快点

209
00:14:24,930 --> 00:14:27,990
- Yeah. Yes, sir. - Ready?
-好，是的 -好了吗？

210
00:14:28,860 --> 00:14:32,730
- What the hell are you still doing here? - I think you know!
-你还在这里做什么呢？ -我想你知道

211
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:37,500
- Oh, you sick bastard! - I am what you made me! Know what?
-喔，你该死的浑蛋！ -这都是你造成的，你知道吗？

212
00:14:37,670 --> 00:14:40,400
- What? - I could go right now.
-什么？ -我可以现在就走

213
00:14:42,610 --> 00:14:48,450
- Then go. Go! - Oh, I can't. I want to, but I can't!
-那就走，走啊！ -喔，我不行，我很想，但是我不行！

214
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:53,850
Cut. That was good!
停，演得好！

215
00:14:54,020 --> 00:14:57,550
- Very good. You did everything I asked. - I did?
-非常精采，你做到我的要求了 -是吗？

216
00:14:57,730 --> 00:15:01,320
Yes. Plus which, you've got this, I don't know, this squirmy quality..
是的，而且你把这种... 扭曲的特质...

217
00:15:01,830 --> 00:15:04,460
you bring to the character I couldn't have imagined.
加入到这个角色中 我想都没想过

218
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:06,190
Here's what we're gonna do:
我们接下来可以这样…

219
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:08,890
Come back tomorrow for the final callbacks.
明天过来参加最后的试演

220
00:15:09,070 --> 00:15:12,200
Do all of this, what you got going now. But you know what?
照你今天演的，但是你知道吗？

221
00:15:12,370 --> 00:15:13,930
More. More. Can you do that?
加强，再加强，你可以吗？

222
00:15:14,110 --> 00:15:18,440
Sure. I don't have time to say thank you because I really gotta go!
当然，我没有时间说谢了 我真的得走了！

223
00:15:19,910 --> 00:15:23,870
Look at that! Still in character. I like him.
瞧瞧他！还那么入戏，我喜欢他

224
00:15:24,050 --> 00:15:28,850
I plant seeds. I can't explain it. I don't know.
我播了种，快得无法解释 我不知道

225
00:15:33,060 --> 00:15:35,860
- Hey. What are you doing? - Putting on the sneakers..
-嘿，你在做什么？ -在试穿步鞋

226
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:38,730
to get in the young mindset, see if it sparks anything.
融入年轻人的世界 看会不会激发出什么点子

227
00:15:38,930 --> 00:15:41,630
- Oh, anything yet? - Yes, how's this?
-喔，想出什么了吗？ -是的，听听看这个

228
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:46,870
"They're so uncomfortable, it's like getting kicked in the nuts for your feet."
“它们舒服到就像是 被脚踢到蛋蛋一样”

229
00:15:49,848 --> 00:15:52,009
-Hi! -Hi!
-嘿！ -嘿！

230
00:16:00,490 --> 00:16:03,080
You're probably wondering what I'm doing.
你可能很纳闷，不知道我在做什么

231
00:16:03,390 --> 00:16:04,880
No, that seems about right.
不，看起来很正常

232
00:16:05,890 --> 00:16:10,690
Yesterday at my audition, I had to pee. Apparently, that makes me a good actor.
昨天在试演的时候我好想尿尿 很明显地，那让我演的很棒

233
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:13,890
I got a callback, so I'm drinking everything. Oh, by the way..
可以参加最后试演 所以我要喝多一点东西，对了

234
00:16:14,030 --> 00:16:16,400
that eggnog in our fridge was great!
我们冰箱里面的蛋奶实在太好喝了

235
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:21,130
- Joey, that was formula. - We gotta get more of that.
-乔伊，那是特调婴儿奶粉 -我们一定要多买一些

236
00:16:23,110 --> 00:16:27,440
These aren't half bad. You should suggest these to Ralph Lauren.
这些东西挺不错的 你应该要向洛夫罗伦推荐

237
00:16:27,650 --> 00:16:32,780
Okay, first of all, that's stupid. Second, I'm not allowed to talk to Ralph.
好的，第一，那很蠢 再来，他们不允许我跟洛夫说话

238
00:16:33,190 --> 00:16:38,220
All right. I feel younger already.
好的，我已经开始觉得年轻多了

239
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:43,450
Yeah, I think I broke my hip.
我想我摔伤臀部了

240
00:16:44,830 --> 00:16:46,320
- Hey, you! - Hey.
-嘿，你来了 -嘿

241
00:16:46,530 --> 00:16:49,060
Hey. How was class?
嘿，课上得怎样？

242
00:16:49,870 --> 00:16:52,000
No one asks me that. What's wrong?
没有人这样问过我，怎么了？

243
00:16:53,170 --> 00:16:56,200
- Nothing. I really want to know. - Oh.
-没事，我真的想知道而已 -喔

244
00:16:56,380 --> 00:17:00,750
Well, there was actually a rather lively discussion about the Pleistocene..
我们针对更新世 有很热烈的讨论

245
00:17:00,980 --> 00:17:03,470
All right, nothing is worth this.
好了，我不需要这样折磨自己

246
00:17:04,690 --> 00:17:07,380
I have a confession to make.
我有件事需要对你坦白

247
00:17:07,550 --> 00:17:10,580
Okay, you know that girl that mugged you when you were a kid?
你记得那个在你小时候 抢劫过你的女生吗？

248
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:16,490
What are you talking about? It wasn't a girl. It was this huge dude.
你在说什么呢？那不是女生 是个高壮的男生

249
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:20,860
He had a pitchfork and a sword.
他带着草耙，还有一把剑

250
00:17:22,140 --> 00:17:25,590
You don't have to lie anymore. I know that it was a 14-year-old girl.
你不需要说谎了 我知道是个十四岁女生

251
00:17:25,810 --> 00:17:27,330
- No, it wasn't. - Yes, it was.
-不，不是 -是，是的

252
00:17:27,540 --> 00:17:31,710
You don't think I would have defended myself against a 14-year-old..?
你认为我不会反抗 一个十四岁女生吗？

253
00:17:31,950 --> 00:17:35,640
- "Give me your money, punk!" - Oh, my God, it was you!
-“小子！钱交出来” -我的天，那是你！

254
00:17:37,180 --> 00:17:41,120
I can't believe it. You mugged me?
我真不敢相信，你抢劫我

255
00:17:41,860 --> 00:17:45,350
Yeah. And I'm so, so sorry, Ross. I'm sorry.
是的，而且我很抱歉，罗斯 我很抱歉

256
00:17:45,530 --> 00:17:48,290
But, you know, if you think about it, it's kind of neat.
但是如果你仔细想想，这倒是有点酷

257
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:54,130
I mean, well, it's just that I've always felt kind of like an outsider.
我是说，我常常觉得我像是个局外人

258
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:57,830
You know, the rest of you have connections that go way back..
你们其他的人都彼此认识很久了

259
00:17:58,010 --> 00:18:02,640
and, you know, now you and I have a great one.
而现在，你跟我也有老交情了

260
00:18:03,740 --> 00:18:05,580
It's not the best!
这并不是好事！

261
00:18:06,580 --> 00:18:09,880
I know. Please forgive me. I don't know what to say.
我知道，请原谅我，我不知道该说什么

262
00:18:10,080 --> 00:18:13,820
There's nothing you can say! That was the most humiliating thing ever.
你不用说什么！那是我这辈子 最可耻的事了

263
00:18:14,020 --> 00:18:17,220
- Even more humiliating than.. - Let's not do this!
-甚至比… -我们不要说了！

264
00:18:20,330 --> 00:18:24,060
And then, at the end of the commercial, the girls get out of the hot tub..
然后在广告结尾，女孩子们离开浴池

265
00:18:24,230 --> 00:18:26,700
and start making out with each other.
开始一起亲热

266
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:31,270
That's interesting.
有趣

267
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:35,330
Just one thought: You didn't mention the shoes.
顺便提一下，你没有提到鞋子

268
00:18:37,680 --> 00:18:40,480
Who's next? Chandler.
下一个是谁？钱德

269
00:18:40,980 --> 00:18:43,470
You start with a guy putting on the shoes.
一开始有个男的穿上这鞋

270
00:18:43,620 --> 00:18:45,680
- He's about my age. - Your age?
-他大约是我的年纪 -你的年纪？

271
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:51,250
He's rolling down the street and he starts to lose control.
他在街上滑行着，接着就失去控制

272
00:18:51,430 --> 00:18:53,990
Maybe he falls. Maybe he hurts himself.
或许他跌倒了，或者受伤了

273
00:18:54,130 --> 00:18:57,860
Just then, a kid comes flying by wearing the shoes.
就在这时候，有个小孩 穿着这双鞋飞过去

274
00:18:58,030 --> 00:19:01,630
He jumps over the old guy and laughs. And the line reads:
他跳过那个老男人，然后大笑 接着广告词出现…

275
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:04,530
"Not suitable for adults."
“成人不宜”

276
00:19:05,410 --> 00:19:09,360
- Well, Chandler, that's great. - Thank you, sir.
-钱德，这个很棒 -谢谢你，先生

277
00:19:09,540 --> 00:19:13,210
Or, man who's two years younger than me.
或是，比我小两岁的人

278
00:19:13,810 --> 00:19:18,620
You see, that has a clear selling point. It appeals to our key demographic.
你们瞧，销售讯息很清楚 抓住了我们主要客户群的心态

279
00:19:18,790 --> 00:19:21,780
- How did you come up with that? - I don't know! I don't know!
-你是怎么想出来的呢？ -我不知道！我不知道！

280
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:27,660
I was just trying to get into a young mindset, and stuff started to flow.
我只是设法用年轻的心态去思考 然后点子就出现了

281
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:32,530
- That is great. Good work. - Thank you.
-太棒了，做得好 -谢谢

282
00:19:32,730 --> 00:19:35,400
We'll see all of you tomorrow.
那我们大家明天见

283
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:48,180
The cold weather hurts my hip.
冷天让我的臀部很痛

284
00:19:52,290 --> 00:19:58,750
Hey, Ross. I know you're still mad at me, but can I just talk to you for a sec?
嘿，罗斯，我知道你还在生我的气 但是我可以跟你谈一下吗？

285
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:03,590
Sure, go ahead. Oh, sorry. Sure, go ahead.
当然，说吧，喔，等等 当然，说吧

286
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:06,930
I just really wanted to apologize again.
我真的想要再次跟你道歉

287
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:11,940
And also show you something I think you'll find very exciting.
而且让你看些 你会觉得很兴奋的东西

288
00:20:12,110 --> 00:20:13,475
（街上的垃圾）

289
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:17,580
Oh, my God! "Crap from the street!"
喔，我的天啊！“街上的垃圾！”

290
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:24,310
Look, Ross. In this box..
听着，罗斯，在这箱子里

291
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:29,080
are all the things I got from mugging that I thought were too special to sell..
都是在抢来的东西之中 我觉得太特别，而不想卖掉…

292
00:20:29,220 --> 00:20:31,190
or smoke.
或是烧掉的东西

293
00:20:32,730 --> 00:20:35,720
Anyway, I was looking through it, and I found..
反正，我在整理时发现了…

294
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:38,190
Science Boy.
《科学小子》

295
00:20:39,670 --> 00:20:42,970
Oh, my God!
喔，我的天啊！

296
00:20:44,670 --> 00:20:47,500
